KwaZulu-Natal police are still searching for a four-year-old girl and hijackers who abducted her inside her father’s vehicle in Pinetown, west of Durban, on Saturday. KZN police spokesperson Thembeka Mbhele says the child was travelling with her father when unknown suspects hijacked him at gun point. She says they then drove away with the child. “The driver of a VW was driving along Portshepstone Road in Pinetown when he was hijacked by unknown suspects. They took his vehicle and he was travelling with his four year old daughter. The child has not been found and the police are still looking for the child and the vehicle,” Mbhele explained. 